<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-585-987  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 585 987.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  May 8 1989 n314 p60(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Taking sales off hold: telemarketing opens doors.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shore, Joel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Many companies are turning to microcomputer-based telemarketingsystems to improve the efficiency of their sales staff and toreduce costs.andP;  Current cost of an on-site sales call is $300 ormore.andP;  A telemarketing system, with crucial information accessibleat the press of a key, reduces the cost of a call to about $30.andO;Features of these packages include call scheduling, sales leadtracking, autodial, call history, client profile, scripting andfacsimile interface.andP;  Some packages allow the user to generateprice quotes or actual sales orders.andP;  Connections to other systemsallow the order to generate merchandise packing slips, shippingdocuments and invoices.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TelemarketingSales ManagementMarketingSoftware.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>